  "body": "Running the latest windows 1.5.3 binaries for windows. After a while the following  exception occurs. This looks like it has something to do with the '--cache' setting. Having it there eventually leads to a crash\r\n\r\nC:\\>C:\\geth.exe --rpc --cache=1024\r\n--\r\nI1125 04:05:03.849917 node/node.go:410] HTTP endpoint opened: http://localhost:8545                                                                                    I1125 04:05:20.594812 eth/downloader/downloader.go:326] Block synchronisation started\r\nI1125 04:06:46.131355 core/blockchain.go:1042] imported 2 blocks,    19 txs (  2.442 Mg) in   13.428s ( 0.182 Mg/s). #2687328 [cad2b762… / 1e71d2b6…]\r\nfatal error: out of memory\r\n\r\nruntime stack:\r\nruntime.throw(0xcf7127, 0xd)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/panic.go:566 +0x7f\r\nruntime.(*mcache).refill(0x1df0000, 0x4, 0x57e83fd8)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/mcache.go:123 +0xd2\r\nruntime.(*mcache).nextFree.func1()\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/malloc.go:505 +0x2b\r\nruntime.systemstack(0x138a6000)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/asm_386.s:323 +0x5e\r\nruntime.mstart()\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/proc.go:1079\r\n",
